article.headline: Santa Clara 71, Pepperdine 59
article.story: MALIBU, Calif. -- Marc Trasolini scored seven of his game-high 18 points in helping Santa Clara jump to a 26-5 lead, and the Broncos went on to a 71-59 victory at Pepperdine on Thursday night. Trasolini hit 7 of 9 shots from the floor and had eight rebounds for Santa Clara (13-9, 4-2 West Coast Conference). Evan Roquemore added 14 points, Niyi Harrison 12 points and Troy Payne 11. Mychel Thompson had 17 points and Joshua Lowery 12 for Pepperdine (8-15, 2-4). Santa Clara broke out to a 17-1 lead as the Waves didn't hit a field goal until 4 1/2 minutes into the game. The Broncos went into halftime with a 33-18 lead, and Pepperdine got no closer than 12 points in the second half.
